ound: #ddffdd;\" align=\"center\"\n| 15 || December 10, 2000 || [[Minnesota Vikings]] || '''W''' 40\u201329 || 3:15&nbsp;p.m. || [[Trans World Dome]] || FOX || Pat Summerall & John Madden || 9\u20135 || <center>66,273</center>\n|-\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\" align=\"center\"\n| 16 || December 18, 2000 || at [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] || '''L''' 35\u201338 || 8:00&nbsp;p.m. || [[Raymond James Stadium]] || [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] || Al Michaels, Dan Fouts & Dennis Miller || 9\u20136 || <center>65,653</center>\n|-\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\" align=\"center\"\n| 17 || December 24, 2000 || at '''[[New Orleans Saints]]''' || '''W''' 26\u201321 || 12:00&nbsp;p.m. || [[Louisiana Superdome]] || FOX || Dick Stockton & Matt Millen || 10\u20136 || <center>64,900</center>\n|-\n|colspan=9 align=\"center\"| '''''[[2000\u201301 NFL playoffs|Postseason]]'''''\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\" align=\"center\"\n| 18 || December 30, 2000 || at [[New Orleans Saints]] (3) || '''L''' 28\u201331 || 3:15&nbsp;p.m. || [[Louisiana Superdome]] || [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] || Al Michaels, Dan Fouts & Dennis Miller || 10\u20137 || <center>64,900</center>\n|-\n|}\nThe Rams' 31-24 loss to the [[New Orleans Saints]] on November 26 marked the first time ever for a quarterback (the Saints' [[Aaron Brooks (American football)|Aaron Brooks]]) defeating the defending Super Bowl champions at their home field in his first career NFL start.\n\n===Season summary===\n\n====Week 1====\n\n{{AFB game box start\n|Title=\n|Visitor=Broncos\n|V1=7 |V2= 10|V3=10 |V4=9\n|Host='''Rams'''\n|H1=7 |H2=14 |H3=14 |H4=6\n|Date=September 4\n|Location=[[TWA Dome]], [[St. Louis, Missouri]]\n|StartTime=8:00 p.m.\n|TimeZone=CST\n|ElapsedTime=\n|Attendance=\n|Weather=indoors (dome)\n|Referee=[[Gerald Austin]]\n|TVAnnouncers= [[Al Michaels]], [[Dan Fouts]], [[Dennis Miller]], [[Melissa Stark]], [[Eric Dickerson]]\n|TVStation=ABC\n}}\n*'''Source:''' [https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/200009040ram.htm Pro-Football-Reference.com]\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |FirstEntry=yes |Quarter=1 |Time= |Team=DEN |Event=Griese 8-yard run (Elam kick) |Score=Broncos 7\u20130}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=1 |Time= |Team=STL |Event=Hakim 86-yard punt return (Wilkins kick) |Score= Tie 7\u20137}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=2 |Time= |Team=DEN |Event=Elam 32-yard field goal |Score= Broncos 10\u20137}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=2 |Time= |Team=STL |Event=Faulk 5-yard run (Wilkins kick) |Score= Rams 14\u201310}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=2 |Time= |Team=DEN |Event=R. Smith 25-yard pass from Griese (Elam kick) |Score= Broncos 17\u201314}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=2 |Time= |Team=STL |Event=Proehl 7-yard pass from Warner (Wilkins kick) |Score= Rams 21\u201317}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=3 |Time= |Team=DEN |Event=Elam 38-yard field goal |Score=Rams 21\u201320}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=3 |Time= |Team=STL |Event=Faulk 72-yard pass from Warner (Wilkins kick) |Score= Rams 28\u201320}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=3 |Time= |Team=STL |Event=Hakim 80-yard pass from Warner (Wilkins kick) |Score= Rams 35\u201320}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=3 |Time= |Team=DEN |Event=D. Clark 7-yard pass from Griese (Elam kick) |Score= Rams 35\u201327}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=4 |Time= |Team= DEN|Event=Elam 36-yard field goal |Score= Rams 35\u201330}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=4 |Time= |Team= DEN|Event=Buckley 32-yard interception return (two-point conversion failed) |Score=Broncos 36\u201335}}\n    {{AFB Game Box Scoring Entry |Quarter=4 |Time= |Team= STL|Event=Holcombe 1-yard run (pass failed) |Score=Rams 41\u201336 |LastEntry=yes}}\n{{AFB game box end}}\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n===Standings===\n{{2000 NFC West standings}}\n\n===Best performances===\n* Marshall Faulk, October 15, 208 rushing yards vs. Atlanta Falcons\n